<p><strong>Bug A</strong> — The border should flash for a moment then go back to grey, but once it flashes it stays red forever.</p>
<pre><code class="language-python">if ship_x &gt; WIDTH - 20:
    ship_x = WIDTH - 20
    flash_timer = 10
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> the timer is set but never counts down.</p>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code (show where the timer goes down):</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
